    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Presenting an investment-grade 2001 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-strung S54 3.2L naturally aspirated inline-six. This powerplant utilizes individual throttle bodies and dual-VANOS variable valve timing to achieve a stratospheric 8,000 RPM redline. Power is managed via a tactile Getrag 6-speed manual transmission and a mechanical limited-slip differential. This example is distinguished by its structural integrity, with documented rear subframe reinforcement and a comprehensive VANOS overhaul already completed. The suspension retains its factory-tuned kinematics, offering precise turn-in and exceptional lateral grip. Every component, from the rod bearings to the interior trim, reflects meticulous stewardship. This is a mechanically transparent, unmodified icon ready for the most discerning enthusiast.",
